Synod whisper cells have established a clandestine courier network through the Glasswind Belt, using it to move contraband past Reach Warden inspection points in violation of Violet Compact registry protocols. Couriers carry routing information, ritual keepers maintain the rite infrastructure that disguises the shipments, and lookouts monitor patrol patterns. The Midgaard postmaster requires elimination of one of each to break the current cell's operational capacity.
The Synod whisper cell courier network through the Glasswind Belt has been disrupted. The contraband routing chain is broken, the ritual concealment infrastructure has collapsed, and the lookout network has been cleared. The postmaster has forwarded the disruption report to the Violet Compact registry for cross-reference against known Synod cell activity.

